doc.previous: Songbirds or oscines Suboscines The families are sorted into a somewhat novel sequence unlike that in older works where e g Corvidae are placed last This is because so many reallocations have taken place since about 2005 that a definite taxonomy has not been established yet although the phylogeny is by and large resolved The present sequence is an attempt to preserve as much of the traditional sequence while giving priority to adequately addressing the phylogenetic relationships between the families
